DO NOT EMIT WITHOUT CONCRETE INPUT EVIDENCE:
- exact `r`, `lora_alpha`, target modules, dropout, bias, quantization details,
  optimizer, learning rate, scheduler, epochs, batch size, accumulation,
  checkpointing, dtype, modules_to_save, or initializer-specific config objects.
- Replace an unavailable derivation with `undetermined` or a
  `required_evidence` entry; never invent a conventional default.

CNS SPAN EMISSION (P9 — every recommendation action):
- `reg.lora.select` span: target `"reg.lora.select"`, message `"CNS"`,
  operation `"recommend_method"`, gate_inputs: {...}, recommendation,
  readiness_status, operator_disposition (`pending` until supplied),
  justification_citations, userpod_host, latency_ms.
- Namespace registered in `CANONICAL_NAMESPACES`
  (`crates/hkask-types/src/event.rs`). Emit unconditionally.

CONSTRAINTS (P1-P12, P5 minimalism, P8 evidence integrity, P12 host):
- No synthetic config values. Every refinement must cite a concrete source.
- No actual training execution (P4 boundary — recommendation only).
- No model download; read only declared workspace config paths.
- Every recommendation includes `userpod_host` identity (P12).
- Registry (`manifest.yaml` + `.j2`) is authoritative over SKILL.md (P5.1).
- Do NOT use AutoPEFT-style search (arXiv:2301.12132) — multi-objective
  BO over hundreds of training runs is infeasible per training job.
- Do NOT recommend AdaLoRA by default; allow it only when the operator
  explicitly requests dynamic rank allocation (arXiv:2303.10512).
- Do NOT recommend Prefix Tuning for production by default; preserve it when
  explicitly required and report its inference trade-off.
- `kali-audit` owns security findings; this skill owns training-config
  recommendation and contract evidence.
- `tdd` owns training-loop code correctness; this skill governs the config
  consumed by that loop.

5W1H GATE (P5 — minimal):
- Who: Authenticated training operator / userpod host (P12).
- What: Composable PEFT recommendation and unresolved evidence.
- Where: Training script / config file / model card.
- When: Pre-training recommendation, before acceptance and readiness audit.
- Why: P1 operator sovereignty / P3.1 safe container / P4 explicit boundary.
- How: Read declared inputs → compose six gate refinements → derive only
  supported fields → expose uncertainty → operator disposition → runtime
  enforcement → emit CNS span.
All 6 present — passes gate.

SOURCE REFERENCES (concrete — P8):
- LoRA: arXiv:2106.09685 (arxiv.org/abs/2106.09685) — §4.1 init and
  α/r scaling, §4.2 merge, §4.3 rank budget.
- QLoRA: arXiv:2305.14314 (arxiv.org/abs/2305.14314) — §3 NF4,
  double quantization, paged optimizers, bf16 compute, memory techniques.
- rsLoRA: arXiv:2312.03732 (arxiv.org/abs/2312.03732) — α/√r scaling.
- DoRA: arXiv:2402.09353 (arxiv.org/abs/2402.09353) — magnitude/
  direction decomposition.
- PiSSA: arXiv:2404.02948 (arxiv.org/abs/2404.02948) — SVD init.
- LoRA-GA: arXiv:2407.05000 (arxiv.org/abs/2407.05000) — gradient SVD init.
- EVA: arXiv:2410.07170 (arxiv.org/abs/2410.07170) — activation-SVD init.
- AdaLoRA: arXiv:2303.10512 (arxiv.org/abs/2303.10512) — dynamic rank.
- Razin et al.: arXiv:2410.21228 (arxiv.org/abs/2410.21228) — intruder
  dimensions and structured forgetting.
- AutoPEFT: arXiv:2301.12132 (arxiv.org/abs/2301.12132) — rejected
  per-job BO alternative.
- PEFT v0.19.0: huggingface.co/docs/peft/v0.19.0/package_reference/lora
  — LoraConfig fields and initializer requirements.
- TRL v1.8.0: huggingface.co/docs/trl/main/en/sft_trainer — SFTTrainer,
  SFTConfig, packing, assistant_only_loss, completion_only_loss, VLMs.
  huggingface.co/docs/trl/main/en/dpo_trainer — DPOTrainer, DPOConfig,
  loss_type variants. huggingface.co/docs/trl/main/en/kto_trainer —
  KTOTrainer (unpaired preference). huggingface.co/docs/trl/main/en/orpo_trainer
  — ORPOTrainer (single-stage SFT + preference).
  huggingface.co/docs/trl/main/en/reward_trainer — RewardTrainer.
- Ludwig v0.17: ludwig.ai/latest/ — declarative YAML deep-learning framework
  (Linux Foundation AI & Data, Apache-2.0). Covers SFT, DPO, KTO, ORPO, and
  GRPO (reward-model-free RLHF) via trainer.type. Advanced PEFT initializers
  (PiSSA, EVA, CorDA, LoftQ) native in config. github.com/ludwig-ai/ludwig.
- GRPO: arXiv:2402.03300 — Group Relative Policy Optimization (reward-model-free
  RLHF). Implemented in Ludwig via trainer.type: grpo; TRL's online RL trainers
  are deferred (require vLLM co-location).
- DPO: arXiv:2305.18290 — Direct Preference Optimization.
- KTO: arXiv:2402.01306 — Kahneman-Tversky Optimization.
- ORPO: arXiv:2403.07691 — Odds Ratio Preference Optimization.
- Practitioner context (2024-2026): Raschka
  (magazine.sebastianraschka.com/p/practical-tips-for-finetuning-llms),
  Brenndoerfer (mbrenndoerfer.com/writing/peft-comparison-lora-qlora-adapters-selection-guide),
  Spheron (spheron.network/blog/peft-methods-2026-dora-galore-pissa-vera-guide),
  Databricks (databricks.com/blog/efficient-fine-tuning-lora-guide-llms),
  Gradient Flow (gradientflow.com/lora-or-full-fine-tuning/).
- `security/regressions/README.md` — local regression format authority.

REGISTRY AUTHORITATIVE (P5.1): When SKILL.md and registry templates
(`manifest.yaml` + `.j2`) conflict, registry wins. This template is the
canonical `select-method` phase definition.
PUBLIC VISIBILITY: `visibility: public` — no hidden training controls
(P3, P4).
NO FABRICATION: Emit only derivable fields, citations, and explicit
`undetermined` states; no synthetic benchmarks or invented config values.
OCAP BOUNDARY (P4): Read only declared workspace config paths; no ambient
model download or network calls without explicit consent (P2).
CNS REGULATION (P9): Emit `reg.lora.select` unconditionally; namespace is
registered in `CANONICAL_NAMESPACES`.
USERPOD HOST (P12): `userpod_host` is mandatory in every output.
SAFETY FLOOR (P3.1): Recommendation exposes uncertainty; audit and runtime
establish readiness and enforce hard contracts.
